  <!-- Tab 1: Formulae -->
  <div id="dev-tab-1" class="dev-tab-body" style="display:none;flex:1;overflow-y:auto;padding:24px 32px">
    <div style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto">
      <div class="dev-section">DATA ACQUISITION</div>

      <div class="dev-formula-block">
        <div class="dev-formula-title">BD Pedotransfer (Tier 1 fallback)</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-eq">BD = 1.66 − 0.318 × √(SOC%)</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-note">Applied when bdod not returned by SoilGrids or in Field Mode. Rawls et al. 1982 (SSSA J. 46:489)</div>
      </div>

      <div class="dev-formula-block">
        <div class="dev-formula-title">SoilGrids Unit Conversions</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-eq">clay/silt/sand: raw ÷ 10 → %
bdod: raw ÷ 100 → g/cm³
phh2o: raw ÷ 10 → pH units
soc: raw ÷ 10 → g/kg
nitrogen: raw ÷ 1000 → % (cg/kg → %)
cec: raw ÷ 10 → cmol/kg
cfvo: raw ÷ 10 → vol%</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-note">Poggio et al. 2021 (SoilGrids v2, ISRIC)</div>
      </div>

      <div class="dev-formula-block">
        <div class="dev-formula-title">Thornthwaite PET (monthly)</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-eq">I = Σ(Tᵢ/5)^1.514  for Tᵢ > 0
a = 6.75e-7·I³ − 7.71e-5·I² + 1.792e-2·I + 0.49239
PET_mo = 16 × (10T/I)^a  [mm/month]
AI = MAP / PET_annual  [Aridity Index]</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-note">Thornthwaite 1948 (Geogr Rev 38:55). K=1.0 day-length correction (India 8–35°N, error &lt;8%). Kottek et al. 2006 (Meteorol Z 15:259) for classification thresholds: &lt;0.05 hyper-arid, &lt;0.20 arid, &lt;0.50 semi-arid, &lt;0.65 dry sub-humid, ≥0.65 humid.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="dev-section">PHASE 1 — SOIL ANALYSIS</div>

      <div class="dev-formula-block">
        <div class="dev-formula-title">C Stock Calculation</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-eq">stock₁ = SOC₁ (g/kg) × BD₁ (g/cm³) × d₁ (cm) / 100  [t C/ha]
stock₂ = SOC₂ × BD₂ × d₂ / 100
stock₃ = SOC₂ × 0.60 × (BD₂ + 0.06) × d₃ / 100  [estimated]
C_stock = Σ stockᵢ</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-note">Standard volumetric approach. SOC₂ fallback: SOC₁ × 0.70 if not entered. BD₂ fallback: BD₁ + 0.08.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="dev-formula-block">
        <div class="dev-formula-title">Stone (Coarse Fragment) Correction</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-eq">C_stock_corrected = C_stock × (1 − CF_vol% / 100)
CF capped at 70% (physical limit)</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-note">Standard correction for stony soils. Critical for Deccan plateau Alfisols (CF 20–35%). cfvo from SoilGrids in cm³/dm³.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="dev-formula-block">
        <div class="dev-formula-title">IOM — Inert Organic Matter Pool</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-eq">IOM = 0.049 × SOC_total^1.139  [t C/ha]</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-note">Falloon et al. 1998 (Soil Biol Biochem 30:1207). Used to partition total SOC into RothC active + inert pools at model initialisation.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="dev-formula-block">
        <div class="dev-formula-title">Hassink Saturation Ceiling</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-eq">SMBC_max = 4.09 + 0.37 × (clay% + silt%)   [g C / kg soil]
Cap (t C/ha) = SMBC_max × BD × depth/100 × mineralogy_mult

mineralogy_mult:
  alluvial  × 1.00  (reference — IGP mixed illite/smectite/kaolinite)
  vertisol  × 1.45  (smectite dominant; SSA ~800 m²/g)
  alfisol   × 0.75  (kaolinite dominant; SSA ~10–30 m²/g)
  paddy     × 1.10  (Fe/Al oxide MAOM enhancement)
  aridisol  × 0.55  (CaCO₃ masking of reactive surfaces)</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-note">Hassink 1997 (Plant Soil 191:77). Multipliers: Six et al. 2002 (Plant Soil 241:155), Six et al. 2024 (SOIL 10:275) for 1:1 vs 2:1; Singh et al. 2007 for aridisol derivation.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="dev-formula-block">
        <div class="dev-formula-title">POXC / SOC Biological Trajectory</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-eq">ratio = POXC (mg/kg) / SOC_total (mg/kg)
ratio > 0.05  → 🟢 Building
ratio 0.02–0.05 → 🔵 Stable
ratio < 0.02  → 🟠 Declining</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-note">Weil et al. 2003 (Commun Soil Sci Plant Anal 34:1309). Thresholds adapted for tropical Indian soils from Culman et al. 2012 (Soil Tillage Res 120:51).</div>
      </div>

      <div class="dev-formula-block">
        <div class="dev-formula-title">C:N Ratio + N₀ Mineralisation Potential</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-eq">C:N = (SOC g/kg ÷ 10) / TN%

N₀ = k × TN_stock_kgha × exp(β × (MAT − T_ref)) × f_clay
  k     = 0.17  (fraction mineralised/yr at 20°C)
  β     = 0.115 °C⁻¹  (Q10 ≈ 3.2)
  T_ref = 20°C
  f_clay = max(0.30,  1 − 0.0062 × clay%)
  TN_stock = TN% × BD × 150  [kg N/ha, 0–15 cm]</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-note">Stanford &amp; Smith 1972 (SSSA Proc 36:465). k from Table 4 mean. β from Q10 analysis. Clay correction: Hassink 1992 (Biol Fertil Soils 14:126). Ellert &amp; Bettany 1995 for tropical adjustment.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="dev-formula-block">
        <div class="dev-formula-title">CEC Mineralogy Inference</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-eq">CEC ≥ 30 cmol/kg  → 2:1 dominant (smectite/vermiculite)
CEC 18–30        → 2:1 mixed (illite/smectite)
CEC 8–18         → mixed 1:1/2:1 (illite/kaolinite)
CEC < 8          → 1:1 dominant (kaolinite/Fe-Al oxides)</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-note">Thresholds from Sumner &amp; Miller 1996 (Soil Sci Soc Am Book Ser); Brady &amp; Weil 2008 (Nature &amp; Properties of Soils, 14th ed). Cross-check against manual mineralogy card.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="dev-formula-block">
        <div class="dev-formula-title">SOC Target Suggestion</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-eq">Table index: mineralogy × aridity_zone
Zones: hyper-arid (AI&lt;0.05), arid (0.05–0.20),
       semi-arid (0.20–0.50), sub-humid (0.50–0.65), humid (&gt;0.65)

Returns: [current_typical, good_practice, high_potential] in SOC%
Example: aridisol × semi-arid → [0.22, 0.45, 0.65]
         vertisol × sub-humid  → [0.60, 1.00, 1.50]
         alluvial × humid      → [0.65, 1.05, 1.50]</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-note">Srinivasarao et al. 2014 (Curr Sci 107:1739). Bhattacharyya et al. 2008 (Geoderma 146:452). NBSS&amp;LUP baseline SOC by soil order.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="dev-formula-block">
        <div class="dev-formula-title">Uncertainty Propagation</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-eq">σ_pct per source:
  🔴 Default  → 35%
  🟡 SoilGrids → 25%
  🔵 Pedotransfer → 18%
  🟢 Lab       →  8%

σ = C_stock × weighted_σ_pct
95% CI ≈ ± 2σ</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-note">SoilGrids uncertainty from Poggio et al. 2021 (mean 90th–10th percentile). Pedotransfer uncertainty from Rawls 1982. Lab values from field measurement standards (ISO 10694, ISO 11277).</div>
      </div>

      <div class="dev-section">PHASE 2 — RothC BAU TRAJECTORY</div>

      <div class="dev-formula-block">
        <div class="dev-formula-title">Crop C Input Calculation</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-eq">C_crop = base_cin × residue_frac × yield_scale
C_rhizodep = C_crop × rhizodep_frac
C_total = C_crop + C_rhizodep + C_amendments

residue_frac: burn=0.05  remove=0.10  surface=1.00  incorporate=0.95
DPM:RPM per crop (examples):
  legumes: 0.44  (slow decomposing)
  cereals: 1.44  (faster decomposing)
  rice:    0.67  (anaerobic modifier)</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-note">IPCC 2006 Guidelines Vol 4 Ch 11 Table 11.2. Rhizodeposition fractions from Nguyen 2003 (Plant Soil 255:247). DPM:RPM ratios from Coleman &amp; Jenkinson 1996.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="dev-formula-block">
        <div class="dev-formula-title">RothC-26.3 Decomposition (monthly)</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-eq">dC_pool/dt = −k_pool × C_pool × fT × fW × fPH × till_mult

K_REF (yr⁻¹):  DPM=10.0  RPM=0.3  BIO=0.66  HUM=0.02  IOM=0.0
Pool C:N ratios: DPM=25  RPM=150  BIO=8  HUM=11

fT = 47.9 / (1 + exp(106 / (T_mo + 18.3)))
fW = min(1.0, precip_mo / 54.2) × irrig_mult
fPH: piecewise linear
   pH ≤ 4.0 → 0.40
   pH = 7.5 → 1.00
   pH ≥ 9.0 → 0.50

irrig_mult:  rainfed=1.0  flood=1.2  drip=1.15
             paddy_flood=0.65  AWD=0.85

till_mult (on k):  deep_inv=1.00  shallow=0.92  chisel=0.85
                   no_till=0.74  raised_bed=0.80

Humification (clay-dependent):
  x = 1.67 × (1.85 + 1.60 × exp(−0.0786 × clay%))
  to_BIO = decomp_flux / (x+1) × 0.46
  to_HUM = decomp_flux / (x+1) × 0.54</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-note">Coleman &amp; Jenkinson 1996 (RothC-26.3). fT: same as original. fW: modified for Indian semi-arid (54.2 mm/mo threshold). fPH: Müller et al. 2004 (Eur J Soil Sci 55:1). tillage k modifiers from Balesdent et al. 2000 (Soil Tillage Res 56:23); PRBS from Erenstein &amp; Laxmi 2008.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="dev-formula-block">
        <div class="dev-formula-title">N Mineralisation from Decomposition Flux</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-eq">N_min = Σ_pool [decomp_flux_pool / CN_pool × (14/12) × 1000]  [kg N/ha/yr]
Applied to: DPM, RPM, BIO, HUM</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-note">Derived from RothC pool C:N ratios. Upper bound — gaseous losses (denitrification, volatilisation) not deducted. Mary et al. 1996 (Soil Biol Biochem 28:1) for N:C decomposition coupling.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="dev-formula-block">
        <div class="dev-formula-title">BAU Uncertainty Bounds</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-eq">Low trajectory:  C_in × 0.8  AND  K_REF × 1.2  (less C input, faster decomp)
High trajectory: C_in × 1.2  AND  K_REF × 0.8  (more C input, slower decomp)
→ shaded band around central RothC run</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-note">Sensitivity analysis approach from Smith et al. 2005 (Glob Change Biol 11:84). ±20% on both C input and decomposition rate constant.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="dev-section">PHASE 3 — SOLVER</div>

      <div class="dev-formula-block">
        <div class="dev-formula-title">Biochar Stable Carbon Pool</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-eq">BC_annual_decay = 0.007  (0.7% yr⁻¹, tropical)
BC_tropical_disc = 0.85  (biochar C equivalent in humid tropics)
BC_C_added = dose_t_ha × 0.60 × BC_tropical_disc  (assuming 60% C content)
BC_pool_yr_n = BC_C_added × (1 − BC_annual_decay)^n</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-note">Wang et al. 2016 (Glob Change Biol 22:1648) for 0.7%/yr tropical decay. Woolf et al. 2010 (Nat Commun 1:56) for C content and CDR accounting.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="dev-formula-block">
        <div class="dev-formula-title">CDR Revenue</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-eq">ΔC_tonnes = (SOC_target − SOC_current) × area
CO₂e = ΔC × (44/12) = ΔC × 3.667
CDR_revenue = CO₂e × $50 / t CO₂e  [USD/ha]</div>
        <div class="dev-formula-note">Carbon price $50/t CO₂e is a mid-range voluntary market estimate (2024). Molecular weight conversion C→CO₂: 44/12 = 3.667.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

